    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SERVICE PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>ADDING REFRIGERANT TO THE SYSTEM</title>
            <para>If it is suspected, during A/C system tests, that the refrigerant charge is too low or too high; it
                will be necessary to perform the following procedures:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>discharge the system, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603003.xml" xrefid="hl1603003">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>;
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>evacuate the system, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603005.xml" xrefid="hl1603005">EVACUATING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>;
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>and recharge the system, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603014.xml" xrefid="hl1603014">CHARGING THE AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM
                            (FULL CHARGE)</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>This method insures that the new refrigerant charge, including refrigerant oil, is accurate.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
